transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I placed an order for Viagra AGB and they sent me, they just sent me the generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: They didn't send me the AGB.

Speaker 1: I'll help you sir, we'll get this fixed. I need your name and zip code to start.

Speaker 2: My name is Barry, B-A-R-R-Y, Burt, B-U-R-T, and my zip code is 95003.

Speaker 1: Thank you sir. You have the pills with you right now?

Speaker 2: Yes I do.

Speaker 1: Do you mind just, so I can confirm over the phone, just read to me what's stamped on an actual pill, just one of the tablets?

Speaker 2: Ah, I'm curious to see, hang on just a sec.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and you're on Lupine Valley Road right?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I believe it says AC339.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you know, you're right, we did send the wrong thing.

Speaker 2: We sell both the regular generic Viagra and then the AGB, so there must have been a mix up somewhere along the way,

Speaker 1: either in the transmitting to the pharmacy or at the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: I do apologize. Those are safe, so if you did take one, you're not going to be harmed in any way.

Speaker 1: But I'm going to get you 20 of the AGB ones.

Speaker 2: Just so you know how I knew that that was wrong, is the AGB pill would say 50 on it.

Speaker 1: Not only should the bottle say AGB on it, but the pill for sure would have said 50.

Speaker 2: Okay, and also the bottle says take one out one hour before.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and good point there.

Speaker 2: The AGB bottle is going to say the same thing, and that's not because it doesn't work faster,

Speaker 1: it's because we can't promise the exact speed for every single person that takes it.

Speaker 2: So to avoid having our customers be in an embarrassing situation the first time or two,

Speaker 1: we do say take it an hour before.

Speaker 2: I would say commonly though I hear it works in about 15 to 20 minutes for most people.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, do you have all my contact information?

Speaker 2: Yeah, 440 Lupine Valley Road in California here.

Speaker 1: So then I'm going to send you out 20 pills.

Speaker 2: I just got to put it in through the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: They will send out 20 of the right ones.

Speaker 2: So like I said, the ones you have are safe if you wanted them as a backup plan,

Speaker 1: but you can toss them if you want to do that too.

Speaker 2: All right, well, I appreciate it. I'm glad I called you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm glad you called too because if there's ever a mistake, we will fix it.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry about that, but it's all fixed now.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you very much. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Of course, Barry. Have a good one.

Speaker 1: All right, bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
